rComments: Gives great lectures and amazing feedback on assignments. Cares about her students and their success in the course.

Professor Brown genuinely cares about her students, providing lectures that are fun and succinct. She is very flexible in providing extensions/feedback, and the opportunity for her students to grow and improve.

Don't hesitate to take Prof. Brown! My favourite so far. She is so funny, kind and really cares about all of her students. Her assignments, quizzes, papers and exams are all extremely fair and she always gives great feedback. An easy class as long as you put in some effort. I learned a lot and greatly enjoyed the class!
She is a friendly and respectful person, but she's a tough grader, and usually, her feedback doesn't make sense, and she has unclear grading criteria.

(Had her for 1131) Prof was very nice and respectful. Every morning she would ask everyone how they were doing. I found that her feedback didn't always make sense though. There is a US version of the Canadian textbook you could use instead of paying but be mindful of the examples because they are different.

Literally the best prof, if you can take a class with her, dont think twice. Treats you like an actual human being and is very caring and understanding. She also marks very fairly, you get the grade you deserve with good feedback. Her course is quite interactive which makes the work load very manageable. 10/10!
Best prof I've had so far! Her grading scheme was so clear and if you screwed up, you always had a chance to make up for it. Super funny and caring, and always available if you need extra help

Dr. Brown is an excellent professor, one of the best Ive had thus far! You must stay on track with her class or itll be easy to fall behind. There is a good amount of work, but nothing difficult, and Ive learnt a lot in her class. Grading criteria is always clear and shes a fair grader who gives good feedback. Take her class if you can!

Prof B is so sweet and caring. She really wants you to do well in her class. The content is very reasonable and easy. Though there is quite a bit of homework but it gives you a chance to boost your grade. Love her accent lol

Dr. Brown is amazing highly recommend. She is so sweet and soft spoken. At the beginning of our discussion groups she would play a song and ask us how we are doing. She really cares about her students. The work for the course was very reasonable, marking was fair and I actually learned a lot from her. She is a queen protect this prof at all costs!!

Dr. Brown is so kind with her students; if you go to her for help, she'll actively try to make sure you succeed. She makes the discussion groups really fun and comfortable, so the classes are really engaging. Textbooks comprise of a grammar handbook and a book on essay writing. The tutorials are attempt-until-you-pass.

literally the best prof I have ever had. she is so sweet and fun and you can tell she genuinely wants her students to do well!! a little bit of a tough marker, but gives great feedback and lots of opportunities to bump up your mark. her lectures are entertaining and engaging and the norton program she uses actually makes the content enjoyable! :)

Prof Brown is fantastic. Her accent is lovely and she is extremely positive. Great range of material but simple, standard brevity assignments. Always available for help outside of class and was accommodating. Wants everyone to do their best and it shows. I want to take more classes with her now and wish I had encountered her sooner! Very fun!

TAKE THIS PROF EVERY CHANCE YOU GET! She is absolutely wonderful! Her grading is extremely clear and fair, and she cares deeply about her students. The assignments were fairly short and straightforward which I loved. Her positive attitude is infections and she is easily one of my favourite profs in the English department.

Amazing Prof! She is so sweet and caring. She is also extremely flexible and willing to give extensions if you ask her. If I could take her for every single course in my degree, I would! If you do the reading and put in the work, it is very possible to get an A+ in the class.

Absolutely amazing professor! She is hilarious and clearly passionate about what she teaches. She is understanding of the difficulties we face as students, esp. during online class. We found out near the end of the term that she would be teaching a new section of a course in the winter and half the class transferred just to be in her class again.
